Kiess institutional monitors have received fresh reports of undead activity across the Chalkwind Saddles route zone — saddle wraiths rising from collapsed caravan ghosts, ice-shelf shades from winter-close casualties, and old tariff enforcer ghosts still running checkpoint protocols at abandoned toll posts. Before Kiess can recommend the Chalkwind route to high-value courier convoys, field agents need current engagement data on all three undead types to confirm their territory and threat class.
The engagement data is filed and Kiess route analysts have updated the Chalkwind threat assessment to reflect active undead presence across three distinct haunting zones. The Saddles are reclassified from cautionary to confirmed-hostile for solo courier runs. The data also confirms that the old tariff enforcer ghost is still running a legitimate-looking checkpoint, which explains why two courier parties reported being turned back by what they described as a uniformed official.
